node.text: 🔢 STATCHAT | The All Blacks scored a total of 6⃣2⃣ tries in 2019. That's an average of 5.1 tries per game!
💥 TEN OF THE BEST | There is no better sight than watching a mullet glide through the air! The countdown of the top ten tries is back with @jack_goodhue and his amazing mullet 💈
🤩 2019 BEST PICS: #5 - @tj_perenara leads the haka in the All Blacks opening match of #RWC2019 against South Africa. 📸: Getty Images

🤩 2019 BEST PICS: #6 - BIG MOOD! Aaron Smith and Sam Cane celebrate a Ben Smith try against Wales at #RWC2019. 📸: Getty Images

📰 NEWS | Ian Foster has confirmed the bulk of his coaching team for the next two years. John Plumtree, Greg Feek and Scott McLeod will all join Foster in the All Blacks coaching team with one more coach to be announced in due course.

Head to allblacks.com for the full story.

New Zealand sport has lost one of its greatest sons. Rest In Peace Sir Peter Snell. Your feats on the track will continue to inspire for generations.
Happy birthday to All Blacks legend Wayne ‘Buck’ Shelford! One of the great leaders of the haka and a talismanic figure on and off the field.
Get well soon Ardie! Leave a message for @ardiesavea below following his knee surgery today! 📸: @ardiesavea
